in this mess in the first place.

01:16:36.791 --> 01:16:37.791
Clarence is right.

01:16:39.208 --> 01:16:40.416
I gotta figure this out.

01:16:51.375 --> 01:16:53.750
-  <i>Apá.</i>
-  What's wrong, baby?

01:16:53.750 --> 01:16:55.083
He got scared.

01:16:55.666 --> 01:16:57.791
Oh, you don't need to be scared.

01:16:57.791 --> 01:16:59.416
The power just went out.

01:16:59.416 --> 01:17:01.666
Plus, your dad's gonna take care
of everything.

01:17:01.666 --> 01:17:03.625
I think I know why it's not selling.

01:17:03.625 --> 01:17:05.458
- What do you mean?
-  The Cheetos.

01:17:06.166 --> 01:17:07.666
They didn't tell anyone it exists.

01:17:07.666 --> 01:17:11.000
There's no commercials,
but there's commercials for everything.

01:17:11.500 --> 01:17:14.541
Cookie Crisp, Sega,
but none for Hot Cheetos.

01:17:14.541 --> 01:17:15.875
I didn't see none.

01:17:16.416 --> 01:17:17.416
Hmm.

01:17:21.000 --> 01:17:22.166
Wait.

01:17:29.375 --> 01:17:30.833
Let's buy a commercial.

01:17:31.833 --> 01:17:34.833
I know it's not a lot, but it's a start.

01:17:35.875 --> 01:17:38.666
<i>This little</i> mocoso
<i>was giving me his lunch money,</i>

01:17:38.666 --> 01:17:41.000
<i>his recycling money, everything.</i>

01:17:41.750 --> 01:17:43.541
<i>And I wasn't gonna take it.</i>

01:17:43.541 --> 01:17:44.791
All right.

01:17:44.791 --> 01:17:46.625
<i>But I was gonna take his idea.</i>

01:17:47.500 --> 01:17:49.500
Hey! I'm gonna get your job back, big dog!

01:17:50.000 --> 01:17:51.083
But I need your help.

01:17:51.958 --> 01:17:53.000
Little busy here, bro.

01:17:55.166 --> 01:17:56.875
This way, Mrs. Romero.

01:17:56.875 --> 01:18:00.083
I got an idea, but I need you guys
to do what you do best.

01:18:00.083 --> 01:18:02.000
Oh, yeah? What's that?

01:18:03.541 --> 01:18:05.208
A little guerrilla marketing.

01:18:05.208 --> 01:18:08.041
<i>Man, these fools didn't have
no business degrees,</i>

01:18:08.041 --> 01:18:10.000
<i>but they could sell condoms to a nun.</i>

01:18:10.000 --> 01:18:13.666
<i>They could close a hundred sales in a day.
They move product like G's.</i>

01:18:32.291 --> 01:18:33.625
Hey, stick around!

01:18:33.625 --> 01:18:35.791
Everybody, come here!
Come close! Bring it in!

01:18:35.791 --> 01:18:36.958
Come on in!

01:18:38.500 --> 01:18:40.500
-<i>Oigan!</i> Listen up!
- Hector! Alejandro!

01:18:40.500 --> 01:18:41.875
-  Gino!

01:18:42.458 --> 01:18:43.583
Come on, everybody.

01:18:43.583 --> 01:18:45.250
- I like your hairnet. <i>Firme.</i>
-  Come on!

01:18:46.125 --> 01:18:48.333
I got something to say!
Everybody needs to hear this!

01:18:48.333 --> 01:18:49.708
Montañez.

01:18:49.708 --> 01:18:52.583
That is not safe or sanitary.
Get down from there right now.

01:18:52.583 --> 01:18:54.250
Back up. Not today. Okay, Lonny?

01:18:55.500 --> 01:18:56.500
Not today.

01:18:57.000 --> 01:18:59.166
Yeah, I was backing up.

01:19:00.416 --> 01:19:01.791
Corporate's killing the product.

01:19:01.791 --> 01:19:03.250
- What?
- Aw, man.

01:19:03.250 --> 01:19:04.541
No. I know! I know!

01:19:05.208 --> 01:19:07.291
But it's not because
the people don't love it.

01:19:07.291 --> 01:19:10.500
If people knew it existed,
it would be huge.

01:19:11.083 --> 01:19:13.208
Like, yeah, we can let it die.

01:19:13.208 --> 01:19:15.208
We can let the factory get shut down...

01:19:16.416 --> 01:19:19.166
...or we can pick ourselves up
and show 'em who we are.

01:19:19.916 --> 01:19:21.833
I ain't got no fancy degrees.

01:19:21.833 --> 01:19:23.041
None of us do.

01:19:23.041 --> 01:19:24.166
We don't need 'em,

01:19:24.166 --> 01:19:25.666
because people like us,

01:19:26.416 --> 01:19:27.791
like you and me,

01:19:28.458 --> 01:19:30.375
we're what makes this whole thing run.

01:19:31.166 --> 01:19:34.000
None of this exists if we don't exist.

01:19:35.416 --> 01:19:37.250
Let's show 'em that we won't be buried.

01:19:37.250 --> 01:19:39.583
Shut up, Montañez!
You trying to get us all fired?

01:19:39.583 --> 01:19:42.333
Hey! Let the man speak.

01:19:43.083 --> 01:19:44.083
Go on, brother.

01:19:44.083 --> 01:19:46.000
I'm not trying to get you fired.

01:19:46.000 --> 01:19:47.916
I'm asking you to save your job.

01:19:48.500 --> 01:19:51.291
Because if we don't,
that's it for all of us.

01:19:52.375 --> 01:19:55.083
And this product doesn't only have
the Montañez name on it.

01:19:55.666 --> 01:19:57.375
It's got the Romero name.

01:19:57.875 --> 01:19:59.916
- Morales.
- Hey.

01:19:59.916 --> 01:20:01.541
Baker.

01:20:02.208 --> 01:20:04.291
- Listen.
- And Carson.

01:20:06.708 --> 01:20:09.291
Enrico believes that we're
what make this company special.

01:20:10.583 --> 01:20:12.916
So we can sit around
like a bunch of <i>huevónes</i>...

01:20:14.250 --> 01:20:17.166
or we can stand up and be great.

01:20:17.958 --> 01:20:20.666
What exactly are
you asking for here, Montañez?

01:20:21.250 --> 01:20:23.750
I need all the product that didn't sell
loaded up into the trucks.

01:20:23.750 --> 01:20:25.000
Everyone who's got the time,

01:20:25.000 --> 01:20:27.333
before or after your shifts,
whatever it takes.

01:20:27.333 --> 01:20:30.291
We're gonna distribute it.
We're gonna get it out to our people.

01:20:39.458 --> 01:20:40.708
Well, you heard the man!

01:20:41.375 --> 01:20:44.500
Get up, line up, and let's get
this product on those trucks. Let's go!

01:20:44.500 --> 01:20:46.333
-  <i>Ándele!</i>

01:20:48.375 --> 01:20:50.291
-  Let's load up!
-  Let's move.

01:20:50.291 --> 01:20:52.625
Hey, Hector, get the truck! Let's go!

01:20:58.708 --> 01:20:59.541
Take that.

01:21:06.208 --> 01:21:07.291
Grab a box!

01:21:07.291 --> 01:21:09.791
Everybody, come on in!
We're gonna load up all the cars!

01:21:09.791 --> 01:21:11.250
Move down the line.

01:21:11.250 --> 01:21:12.916
Here we go! Here we go!

01:21:12.916 --> 01:21:15.000
Drop the box, go get another one.

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:17.208
- Pack them in there tight, guys.
-  Here you go.

01:21:18.666 --> 01:21:19.916
Drop a box.

01:21:19.916 --> 01:21:22.750
- Get back in and get another one.
-  More boxes on this side!

01:21:22.750 --> 01:21:23.833
Can I?

01:21:26.291 --> 01:21:27.416
Wow.

01:21:31.041 --> 01:21:33.541
-  Thank you, hon.

01:21:33.541 --> 01:21:34.666
What's up?

01:21:35.250 --> 01:21:37.041
- Hi, mama.
- Hey, can I have one?

01:21:40.416 --> 01:21:42.625
Here's another one.
Tell all your family too.

01:21:42.625 --> 01:21:44.625
Cheetos! Get 'em.
Get your Cheetos!

01:21:45.666 --> 01:21:47.875
- Hey, my son made those.
- You must be proud, eh?

01:21:47.875 --> 01:21:49.541
Yeah, tell your friends.

01:21:49.541 --> 01:21:52.000
- You're gonna love them.
-  Get your Flamin' Hot Cheetos!

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:53.916
Hey! Flamin' Hot Cheetos!

01:21:57.708 --> 01:21:58.833
Big sister.

01:21:59.500 --> 01:22:00.625
The convenience store.

01:22:01.708 --> 01:22:03.500
- Enjoy.
- Bro, check it out!

01:22:05.708 --> 01:22:07.458
They're different because they're spicy.

01:22:07.458 --> 01:22:08.541
 Hot Cheetos!

01:22:09.083 --> 01:22:11.791
Guys, guys!
Come here! Come here! Hot Cheetos.

01:22:11.791 --> 01:22:14.500
- Guys, guys. Hey, wait up. Hot Cheetos.
- Hot Cheetos. Come here.

01:22:15.583 --> 01:22:18.083
- Here, here! Take 'em.
- Hey, thank you, little man.

01:22:18.083 --> 01:22:19.000
Thanks.

01:22:19.000 --> 01:22:21.041
-  Hey, guys. Try these.
-  Excuse me.

01:22:21.041 --> 01:22:22.291
So good. Try these.

01:22:22.291 --> 01:22:25.375
Hey. We just made these. They're Cheetos
with <i>chile</i> on them. You gotta try 'em.

01:22:25.375 --> 01:22:26.750
- Are you serious?
- Yeah, they're crazy.

01:22:26.750 --> 01:22:28.875
- Your kids are gonna love 'em.
- Thank you.

01:22:28.875 --> 01:22:30.875
Here! Tell all your homegirls.

01:22:33.583 --> 01:22:35.916
Hey! Hold up. Hold up. Hold Up.

01:22:35.916 --> 01:22:39.083
Hey, we got something for you to try.
The next one you gotta buy, all right?

01:22:39.083 --> 01:22:42.291
What I say? I said, one bag each.

01:22:42.291 --> 01:22:44.083
One bag each. We ain't trying to waste it.

01:22:44.083 --> 01:22:46.500
- Let 'em enjoy it. What's up?
-  Call 'em back.

01:22:46.500 --> 01:22:47.583
Right here!

01:22:47.583 --> 01:22:48.916
Hey, watch it!

01:22:55.750 --> 01:22:57.083
They're obsessed.

01:22:57.083 --> 01:22:58.458
They're my new favorite.

01:22:59.041 --> 01:23:00.500
They're so good.

01:23:00.875 --> 01:23:01.875
 What are they?

01:23:02.416 --> 01:23:03.708
Cheetos <i>con chile</i>.

01:23:03.708 --> 01:23:04.791
They're flamin' hot.

01:23:04.791 --> 01:23:05.958
Oh.

01:23:09.291 --> 01:23:10.458
Can I get a bag?

01:23:10.458 --> 01:23:13.416
<i>Maybe it looked like a bunch
of Mexicans hustling the streets</i>

01:23:13.416 --> 01:23:15.750
<i>to move a few bags, but the truth was,</i>

01:23:15.750 --> 01:23:18.875
<i>we were mobilizing the Hispanic market
before we even knew what it was.</i>

01:23:18.875 --> 01:23:20.041
All right!

01:23:21.708 --> 01:23:23.541
<i>So Enrico wanted answers.</i>

01:23:24.333 --> 01:23:26.000
<i>"How are you gonna explain this, fool?</i>

01:23:26.500 --> 01:23:30.625
<i>How's Hot Cheetos got more love on it
than your</i> ruca <i>has got</i> vatos <i>on her,</i> ese<i>?"</i>

01:23:30.625 --> 01:23:33.250
<i>Finley was shitting his pants.
So he was like,</i>

01:23:33.250 --> 01:23:36.000
<i>"Man, I don't know
what you're talking about, homes.</i>

01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:38.458
<i>I ain't never heard
of none of these</i> tonterías<i>."</i>

01:23:38.458 --> 01:23:42.083
<i>But Al Carey wasn't having it.
So he got super gangster and was like,</i>

01:23:42.083 --> 01:23:44.250
<i>"Oh, yeah, you little</i> chavala<i>?</i>

01:23:44.958 --> 01:23:49.708
<i>Yo, Patti, how much</i> lana
<i>did this fool put into the product?"</i>

01:23:49.708 --> 01:23:51.708
<i>Man, even Patti was pissed.</i>

01:23:51.708 --> 01:23:54.583
